description: em- +‎ place. Cognate to French emplacer, Spanish emplazar, Portuguese emplaçar, Catalan emplaçar & Italian impiazzare.

verbs.description: emplace (third-person singular simple present emplaces, present participle emplacing, simple past and past participle emplaced)

entries.meaning: To assign a position to something, or to locate something at a particular place
